1. **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

The main image shows two structures composed of various building blocks.  The structure on the left has three layers. The bottom layer has two identical red blocks, each with an arched cutout, positioned side-by-side. A yellow rectangular block is placed on top of the red blocks. The top layer has two identical red blocks with arched cutouts, identical to those in the bottom layer, placed on top of the yellow block.  The structure on the right has a stack of three blocks: an orange cylindrical block, a yellow rectangular block, and a green rectangular block. Each block is positioned directly on top of the one below.

2. **Select the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:**

* **Needed Blocks:**  Several blocks from the dictionary are necessary to reproduce the structures.
* **List of Block Indices:**
    * **Structure on the Left:**
        * Block 2 (red arched block) - 2x
        * Block 9 (yellow rectangular block) - 1x
    * **Structure on the Right:**
        * Block 13 (red cylindrical block) - 1x
        * Block 10 (yellow rectangular block) - 1x
        * Block 7 (green rectangular block) - 1x
